        "timestamp": "2019-03-20 11:43:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nAdditional declarations would be needed because we do not have (and should not) values for mandatory env/app specific variables in group_vars. E.g. app_name/paths etc.\nAnd for sure we cannot have any defaults for those in any role's defaults.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "a9b79a59cb1730c8ed107913db52b99a753fbd9a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5097,
          "name": "Bartek Grzybowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "b.grzybowski@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "bgrzybowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-20 11:56:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAnd this is exactly the issue i tried to address here gerrit.onap.org/r/c/79625/4/ansible/roles/application-install/defaults/main.yml ! But i was nuked.\n\nNot only above vars could have some default values in role's defaults but vars like app_name also. But they are not so there you go - issues with passing some custom nowhere defined variables...\n\nSo no way to pass application/application_configuration.yml like file to molecule? If really not then again - let's define them in role's defaults...",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "8746e9be300612285413ee79096bcd52fa450dd5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-20 12:24:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> And this is exactly the issue i tried to address here\n > gerrit.onap.org/r/c/79625/4/ansible/roles/application-install/defaults/main.yml\n > ! But i was nuked.\n > \n > Not only above vars could have some default values in role's\n > defaults but vars like app_name also. But they are not so there you\n > go - issues with passing some custom nowhere defined variables...\n > \n > So no way to pass application/application_configuration.yml like\n > file to molecule? If really not then again - let's define them in\n > role's defaults...\n\nYes it was correct nuke.\nWe can handle it in molecule no problem.",
        "patchset_number": 3
